25/05/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- VMRO-DPMNE leader and former Prime Minister Ljubco Georgievski officially resigned at the party's two-day national congress, which opened in Ohrid on Saturday (24 May).
Georgievski said he decided to withdraw in order to give the party the opportunity to improve its image and continue forward.
He pointed to incumbent party deputy chairmen Nikola Gruevski and Marjan Gjorcev as possible successors.
VMRO-DPMNE members are due to elect new party leader on Sunday.About 290 delegates took part in the congress;
representatives of all major political parties attended as guests.
(MIA, A1 TV - 24/05/03)
